Article 1 — Definitions

1. "Software" means all source code, build artifacts, documentation, scripts, and
   related files contained in the hyve repository (github.com/itda-skills/hyve),
   excluding third-party dependencies separately identified in
   THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md, which are governed by their respective licenses.

2. "Student" means a person currently formally enrolled in an offline educational
   course operated by itda-work.

3. "Operator" means the persons who operate and manage itda-work and the
   itda-skills organization.

4. "Official Distribution Channel" means the GitHub Releases at
   github.com/itda-skills/hyve.pub, which is the sole official channel for
   distribution of the Software (ref: SPEC-DIST-008).

5. "Enrollment Period" means the period during which a Student is formally
   enrolled in an itda-work course.

6. "Enrollment End" means the termination of Student status for any reason,
   including course completion, withdrawal, or dismissal.


Article 2 — Grant of License (Students Only)

2.1 This License grants rights to use the Software solely to currently enrolled
    Students. No person other than an enrolled Student may use, install, run,
    copy, or study the Software in any manner without separate written consent
    from the Operator. (REQ-LIC-001 / enrolled student)

2.2 Students are permitted to:
    (a) Install and run the Software for learning and practical exercises within
        the educational course.
    (b) Read the source code and study it for personal learning purposes.
    (c) Modify the source code locally within the scope defined in Article 4.

2.3 This License is non-exclusive, non-transferable, and non-sublicensable.


Article 3 — Prohibited Uses

The following acts are expressly prohibited under this License:

3.1 Commercial Use Prohibited: Use, combine, integrate, or exploit the Software
    for commercial products, paid services, or any revenue-generating activity is
    prohibited. This includes, without limitation, direct sale, provision as SaaS,
    bundling into paid applications, and commercial exploitation in consulting or
    training services. (REQ-LIC-002 / commercial use prohibited)

3.2 Redistribution Prohibited: Distributing, publishing, sharing, or transmitting
    the Software (in source or binary form) through any channel other than the
    Official Distribution Channel (Article 1.4) is prohibited.
    Official Distribution Channel: github.com/itda-skills/hyve.pub GitHub Releases
    (REQ-LIC-003 / redistribution prohibited)

3.3 Distribution of Modified Versions Prohibited: Distributing or publishing
    modified versions of the Software to third parties is prohibited. Upstream
    contributions via Pull Request as required by Article 5 are permitted.

3.4 License Modification Prohibited: Removing or altering this License or any
    copyright notices contained in the Software is prohibited.

3.5 Out-of-Scope Use Prohibited: Using the Software in third-party projects,
    businesses, or organizations unrelated to itda-work courses is prohibited.


Article 4 — Permitted Local Modifications (Learning Purposes)

4.1 Students may modify the Software in their local environment for personal
    learning, bug reproduction, and experimental understanding.
    (REQ-LIC-004 / local modification permitted)

4.2 Local modifications may serve as preparation for fulfilling the contribution
    obligation under Article 5.

4.3 Distributing or publishing locally modified versions to third parties is
    prohibited (Article 3.3).


Article 5 — Contribution Back Obligation (Copyleft-Style)

5.1 Where a Student discovers a bug or implements an improvement in the Software,
    the Student shall contribute that change back to the upstream repository
    (github.com/itda-skills/hyve) via Pull Request within a reasonable period.
    This is a binding obligation, not a mere request.
    (REQ-LIC-005 / contribution obligation — shall contribute)

5.2 This contribution obligation persists after Enrollment End (Article 6.2).

5.3 If a Student declines to contribute a change, that change must not be used,
    retained, or distributed in any form outside the local environment.

5.4 This contribution obligation is a legal condition of this License, not a
    request made in good faith.


Article 6 — Third-Party Dependency Licenses

6.1 The Software includes third-party open-source dependencies governed by
    separate licenses.

6.2 The licenses of all third-party dependencies are listed in
    THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md at the repository root. Such dependencies are governed
    by their respective original licenses.

6.3 The third-party licenses in THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md take precedence over this
    License with respect to the relevant dependencies. (REQ-LIC-006)


Article 7 — Post-Enrollment License Conditions

7.1 Upon Enrollment End, this License automatically converts to the following
    personal learning-only license conditions:
    (REQ-LIC-008 / enrollment end / post-enrollment conditions)

    (a) The Software may be used only for personal, non-commercial learning.
    (b) Commercial use remains prohibited after Enrollment End.
    (c) Redistribution remains prohibited after Enrollment End.
    (d) Local modification is permitted.
    (e) The contribution obligation under Article 5 persists after Enrollment End.

7.2 After Enrollment End, using the Software for employment, business, or services
    for third parties is prohibited without separate written consent from the
    Operator.

7.3 If a former Student re-enrolls in a course, the full rights under Article 2
    are restored for the duration of the new Enrollment Period.


Article 8 — Disclaimer of Warranty

THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR
IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS
FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT. THE OPERATOR MAKES NO WARRANTIES
REGARDING THE SOFTWARE. THE STUDENT ASSUMES ALL RISKS ASSOCIATED WITH USE OF
THE SOFTWARE.


Article 9 — Limitation of Liability

TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, THE OPERATOR SHALL NOT BE
LIABLE FOR ANY DIRECT, INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, PUNITIVE, OR CONSEQUENTIAL
DAMAGES ARISING FROM OR RELATED TO THE USE, MALFUNCTION, OR UNAVAILABILITY OF
THE SOFTWARE. SOME JURISDICTIONS DO NOT ALLOW THE EXCLUSION OF CERTAIN DAMAGES,
SO THE ABOVE LIMITATION MAY NOT APPLY IN FULL.


Article 10 — Language Precedence

This License consists of a Korean primary text and an English translation. In case
of any discrepancy between the Korean and English versions, the Korean version
shall prevail. (REQ-LIC-007)


Article 11 — Governing Law and Jurisdiction

This License shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of
the Republic of Korea. Any dispute arising in connection with this License shall
be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of the Republic of Korea.


Article 12 — License Violation and Termination

Any violation of the terms of this License shall cause all rights granted
hereunder to terminate immediately and automatically. The contribution obligation
under Article 5 shall survive termination with respect to modifications already
made.


